snippet: Obama administration officials said they were assigning new work to contractors in an effort to prevent a repetition of the problems that crippled HealthCare.gov last fall.
abstract: Obama administration officials say work to bolster HealthCare.gov Web site is raising the cost; one-year contract with Accenture that was initially valued at $91 million has increased to $190 million.
lead_paragraph: Obama administration officials said they were assigning new work to contractors in an effort to prevent a repetition of the problems that crippled HealthCare.gov last fall.
